<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,719,2005]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,900,925]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa" authorityName="Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa" box="[328,969,900,925]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ctenocolum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctinotatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[328,623,900,924]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Ctenocolum punctinotatus</emphasis>
Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[975,1065,900,925]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[975,1065,900,925]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is different from 
<taxonomicName authority="Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa" authorityName="Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ctenocolum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygospilotos" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1262,1435,900,924]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">C. pygospilotos</emphasis>
Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[497,587,935,960]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[497,587,935,960]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by having punctures on pygidium moderately impressed (deeply impressed in 
<taxonomicName box="[182,359,972,996]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ctenocolum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygospilotus">
<emphasis box="[182,359,972,996]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">C. pygospilotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and tegmen with U emargination (V emargination in 
<taxonomicName box="[1008,1184,972,996]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ctenocolum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygospilotus">
<emphasis box="[1008,1184,972,996]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">C. pygospilotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). And from the other species by having, in the internal sac of male genitalia, a C-shaped sclerite involved by spicules and a squamous hood-shaped sclerite (
<figureCitation box="[397,481,1044,1069]" captionStart="FIGURES 79 – 84" captionStartId="17.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1372,193,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 79 – 84. Male genitalia, median lobe: 79 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 80 C. colburni; 81 C. martiale (holotype); 82 C. milelo (paratype); 83 C. podagricus; 84 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype). Scale: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698659" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698659/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[449,481,1044,1068]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="84.0">84</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="32" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,719,2005]" box="[199,654,1079,1104]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1079,1104]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Description.</emphasis>
BL: 
<quantity box="[401,491,1079,1104]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
; BW: 
<quantity box="[561,650,1079,1104]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,719,2005]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Integument. Dorsum reddish brown and from dark brown to black. Antenna pale brown (
<figureCitation box="[1275,1374,1116,1141]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1913,1936]" captionTargetBox="[247,1361,252,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[215,1366,193,1885]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 16. Dorsal habitus: 8 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 9 C. biolleyi (holotype); 10 C. colburni; 11 C. martiale (paratype), 12, C. martiale; 13 C. milelo Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 14, C. podagricus; 15 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 16 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype). Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698641" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698641/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Figs. 15</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1392,1424,1116,1141]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 60" captionStartId="11.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[235,1365,234,1880]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 60. Lateral habitus: 53 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 54 C. biolleyi (holotype); 55 C. colburni; 56 C. martiale (paratype); 57 C. milelo (paratype); 58 C. podagricus; 59 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 60 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype). Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698655/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">59</figureCitation>
). Pygidium rufous. Ventral region reddish brown and black. Front and middle femur and tibia pale brown; hind femur from brown, reddish brown to dark.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,719,2005]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Pubescence. Pronotum yellowish gray, brown and white; sparse setae exposing the integument forming an oval, wide area from anterior to posterior region divided by transversal and longitudinal strip of denser setae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1913,1936]" captionTargetBox="[247,1361,252,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[215,1366,193,1885]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 16. Dorsal habitus: 8 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 9 C. biolleyi (holotype); 10 C. colburni; 11 C. martiale (paratype), 12, C. martiale; 13 C. milelo Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 14, C. podagricus; 15 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 16 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype). Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698641" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698641/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,182,1296,1321]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
). Elytra slightly variegated, yellowish gray and white setae; interstria 
<number box="[968,982,1296,1320]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="3.0">3</number>
without white setae (
<figureCitation box="[1223,1307,1296,1321]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1913,1936]" captionTargetBox="[247,1361,252,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[215,1366,193,1885]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 16. Dorsal habitus: 8 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 9 C. biolleyi (holotype); 10 C. colburni; 11 C. martiale (paratype), 12, C. martiale; 13 C. milelo Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 14, C. podagricus; 15 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 16 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype). Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698641" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698641/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[1276,1307,1296,1321]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pygidium white and yellowish gray; probably only with two submedian lateral areas of sparse seta (
<figureCitation box="[1170,1255,1332,1357]" captionStart="FIGURES 35 – 43" captionStartId="8.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1372,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 35 – 43. Pygidium of male: 35 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 36 C. colburni; 37 C. martiale; 38 C. milelo Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 39 C. podagricus; 40 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 41 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 42 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 43 C. acapulcensis. Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698649" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698649/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[1223,1255,1332,1356]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="40.0">40</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ventral region yellowish gray and white (
<figureCitation box="[448,533,1368,1393]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 60" captionStartId="11.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[235,1365,234,1880]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 60. Lateral habitus: 53 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 54 C. biolleyi (holotype); 55 C. colburni; 56 C. martiale (paratype); 57 C. milelo (paratype); 58 C. podagricus; 59 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 60 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype). Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698655/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[501,533,1368,1393]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="59.0">59</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,719,2005]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Head. Ocular sinus 
<quantity box="[423,514,1404,1428]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
; ocular index 8.0; length of eyes in frontal view behind sinus 
<quantity box="[1221,1322,1404,1428]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="0.09">0.09 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[1338,1424,1404,1429]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 30" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1372,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 30. Frontal habitus: 22 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 23 C. biolleyi (paratype); 24 C. colburni; 25 C. martiale; 26 C. milelo Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 27 C. podagricus; 28 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 29 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 30 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype). Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698645" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698645/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1424,1404,1428]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
). Antenna serrate from antennomere 
<number box="[547,602,1440,1464]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="7.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="4.0">4-10</number>
. Frons with frontal carina (
<figureCitation box="[906,990,1440,1465]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 30" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1372,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 30. Frontal habitus: 22 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 23 C. biolleyi (paratype); 24 C. colburni; 25 C. martiale; 26 C. milelo Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 27 C. podagricus; 28 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 29 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 30 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype). Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698645" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698645/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[958,990,1440,1464]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,719,2005]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Prothorax. Pronotum with median gibbosity slightly elevated, not divided by longitudinal and transversal sulcus; lateral gibbosity slightly elevated; basal lobe without depression and slightly emarginated (
<figureCitation box="[1254,1337,1512,1537]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1913,1936]" captionTargetBox="[247,1361,252,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[215,1366,193,1885]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 16. Dorsal habitus: 8 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 9 C. biolleyi (holotype); 10 C. colburni; 11 C. martiale (paratype), 12, C. martiale; 13 C. milelo Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 14, C. podagricus; 15 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 16 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype). Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698641" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698641/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[1306,1337,1512,1537]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,719,2005]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Mesothorax and metathorax. Elytra, striae with punctures deeply impressed; less conspicuous teeth at base of striae 
<number box="[225,239,1584,1608]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="3.0">3</number>
and 
<number box="[306,323,1584,1608]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="4.0">4</number>
; tooth of stria 
<number box="[510,524,1584,1608]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="4.0">4</number>
closer to base of tooth of stria 
<number box="[922,936,1584,1608]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="3.0">3</number>
than to anterior margin of elytra; stria 
<number box="[1422,1436,1584,1609]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="6.0">6</number>
conspicuously impressed. 
<collectingCountry box="[449,505,1620,1645]" name="India" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur (
<figureCitation box="[597,680,1620,1645]" captionStart="FIGURES 72 – 76" captionStartId="14.[151,263,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[216,1383,211,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[200,1387,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 72 – 76. Posterior leg, external view: 72 Ctenocolum punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 73 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 74 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro- Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 75 C. acapulcensis; 76 C. janzeni. Scale: 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286739/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[651,680,1620,1644]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="72.0">72</number>
</figureCitation>
) on external ventral margin with toothed carina; without denticles above of external ventral margin; pecten with 
<number box="[691,705,1657,1680]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="7.0">7</number>
teeth. 
<collectingCountry box="[787,843,1656,1681]" name="India" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia (
<figureCitation box="[921,1006,1656,1681]" captionStart="FIGURES 72 – 76" captionStartId="14.[151,263,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[216,1383,211,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[200,1387,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 72 – 76. Posterior leg, external view: 72 Ctenocolum punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 73 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 74 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro- Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 75 C. acapulcensis; 76 C. janzeni. Scale: 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286739/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[977,1006,1656,1680]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="72.0">72</number>
</figureCitation>
) strongly emarginated beside mucro; lateral coronal denticles present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,719,2005]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Abdomen. Pygidium longer than wide, oval, at median basal region with moderately impressed punctures (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 35 – 43" captionStartId="8.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1372,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 35 – 43. Pygidium of male: 35 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 36 C. colburni; 37 C. martiale; 38 C. milelo Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 39 C. podagricus; 40 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 41 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 42 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 43 C. acapulcensis. Scale: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698649" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698649/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,183,1764,1788]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="40.0">40</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,719,2005]" lastBlockId="32.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="32" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Male genitalia. Median lobe, ventral valve as long as wide, lateral margin concave on subapical region (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 79 – 84" captionStartId="17.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1372,193,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 79 – 84. Male genitalia, median lobe: 79 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 80 C. colburni; 81 C. martiale (holotype); 82 C. milelo (paratype); 83 C. podagricus; 84 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype). Scale: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698659" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698659/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,182,1836,1860]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="84.0">84</number>
</figureCitation>
), basal margin slightly emarginated. Internal sac, lateral apex with short tuft of setae, hinge sclerite inverted Lshape, short, extending over 
<number box="[484,494,1872,1896]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[505,519,1872,1896]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="3.0">3</number>
of subapical region; subapical region with homogeneously distributed spicules, dense in vertical rows forming an elongated strip medially; median region with C- shape sclerite involved by spicules (
<figureCitation box="[257,340,1944,1969]" captionStart="FIGURES 79 – 84" captionStartId="17.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1372,193,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 79 – 84. Male genitalia, median lobe: 79 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 80 C. colburni; 81 C. martiale (holotype); 82 C. milelo (paratype); 83 C. podagricus; 84 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype). Scale: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698659" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698659/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[309,340,1944,1968]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="84.0">84</number>
</figureCitation>
); submedian region with squamous hood- shape sclerite (
<figureCitation box="[987,1071,1944,1969]" captionStart="FIGURES 79 – 84" captionStartId="17.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1372,193,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 79 – 84. Male genitalia, median lobe: 79 Ctenocolum aquilus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 80 C. colburni; 81 C. martiale (holotype); 82 C. milelo (paratype); 83 C. podagricus; 84 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype). Scale: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698659" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698659/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[1040,1071,1944,1968]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="84.0">84</number>
</figureCitation>
); basal region without denticles, spines and spicules. Tegmen (
<figureCitation box="[483,565,1980,2005]" captionStart="FIGURES 91 – 99" captionStartId="19.[151,263,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1372,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[214,1372,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 91 – 99. Male genitalia, tegmen, lateral lobe: 91 C. aquilus (paratype); 92 C. colburni; 93 C. martiale (holotype); 94 C. milelo Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (paratype); 95 C. podagricus; 96 C. punctinotatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 97 C. pygospilotos Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 98 C. triangulatus Albuquerque &amp; Ribeiro-Costa sp. nov. (holotype); 99 C. acapulcensis. Scale: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698663" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698663/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[534,565,1980,2005]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="96.0">96</number>
</figureCitation>
), lateral lobes separated by emargination about 
<number box="[1097,1146,1980,2005]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="0.75">0.75</number>
times the length of lateral lobes; expanded at apex, about 
<number box="[531,566,151,176]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="5.5">5.5</number>
times the smallest width on median region; internal margin near end of emargination curved, forming a &quot;U&quot;; without membranous projection at apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,151,320]" box="[199,688,223,248]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Note. The female and host plants unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1403,260,285]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,151,320]" box="[199,1403,260,285]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,260,285]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name “ 
<emphasis box="[565,732,260,283]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicName box="[565,725,260,283]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Ctenocolum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctinotatus">punctinotatus</taxonomicName>
”
</emphasis>
refers to the punctures deeply impressed on striae of elytra.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,795,295,320]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,151,320]" box="[199,795,295,320]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,295,320]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Distribution.</emphasis>
Neotropical region: 
<collectingCountry box="[585,678,295,320]" name="Ecuador" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(Guayas).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
